@node "Support" "How to support Virushelp team NL and the Vlist!"

   Virushelp team NL likes to ask you to support our team with material
   which is useful for inclusion in this virusscanlist and for supporting
   AV-programmers and testing ALL the known viruskillers.

   VIRUSARCHIVES / FILES:  Please send any virus/trojan/fake/HD formatter/
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~  etc.. to me, pgp encrypted.

                           You can write to me, to request my pgp public
                           key or questions on using pgp.

                           Please contact me before sending any virusfile.

   VIRUSWARNINGS / TEXTS   Please send any viruswarning or virusrelated
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~   text. (see @{" INFO FORMAT " link "Info Format" 0})

   MISSING SPOTS in VLIST  Please send any information about `?' spots in
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~  vlist or any new names of archives / files I
                           may have forgotten.

  @{" YOU CAN CHOOSE BETWEEN THE FOLLOWING E-MAIL ADDRESSES " link "JHL" 0}
@endnode

@node "JHL" "My e-mail addresses: "

   E-MAIL ADDRESSES:
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Internet / Usenet : jhl@grafix.xs4all.nl  (Fast)

   NLA Net           : 14:101/200.20
   FIDO Net          :  2:286/407.20
   LDY Net           : 69:100/102.20

   Unfortunately, Netmail in AMY Net doesn't arrive, so please use another
   available network.
@endnode

@node "Info Format" "Info Format"

   PLEASE USE THE FOLLOWING 'INFO FORMAT' WHEN SENDING INFO:
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   TOPIC:                   EXAMPLE:
   ------                   --------
   Original archive name  : vh!-vir99.lha
   Alias name(s)          : zzx-viral.lzx
   Archive length origin  : 41264 bytes
   Archive length alias   : 63700 bytes
   All filename(s)        : Use lha l option
   All filelength(s)      : idem
   Infected filename(s)   : E1116_infection.exe
                          : Outbreak.exe
   Infected filelength(s) : Please state packed and unpacked lengths and
                          : which was the spreaded form
@endnode

@node "Updates & WWW" "Updates / World Wide Web"

   UPDATES ARE SPREAD IN THE FOLLOWING WAYS:
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   AMINET : <dir> /util/virus/VList137.lha           (GUIDE)
            <dir> /util/virus/VList137_ascii.lha     (ASCII)

   BBS    : Grafix Attack (Virushelp NL Support BBS) (GUIDE + ASCII)

            +31 10 - 4745816 / 4741062 / 4744682

   ELITE  : bOONdOCKs ^ pHANTOm ^ mYSTICAl pLACEs    (GUIDE + ASCII)

   USENET : comp.sys.amiga.misc                      (TXT)
   AMYNET : Virus_Amy                                (TXT + ASCII)
   NLANET : Nla_Virus                                (TXT)

   @{" WORLD WIDE WEB " link "WWW" 0}                (GUIDE + ASCII)
@endnode

